Remove Seasonality

adf.test(original_ts,k=8)
## 
##  Augmented Dickey-Fuller Test
## 
## data:  original_ts
## Dickey-Fuller = -3.6784, Lag order = 8, p-value = 0.02515
## alternative hypothesis: stationary

ACF plot decays to zero gradualy, which means the data is non-stationary.

the data has a trend, seasonal component, apparant shape change(we delete the data 2020)

firstdiff <- diff(original_data[,"CAUR"], diff = 1)

adf.test(firstdiff,k=8)
## Warning in adf.test(firstdiff, k = 8): p-value smaller than printed p-value
## 
##  Augmented Dickey-Fuller Test
## 
## data:  firstdiff
## Dickey-Fuller = -4.1889, Lag order = 8, p-value = 0.01
## alternative hypothesis: stationary
seconddiff <- diff(firstdiff, diff = 1)

adf.test(seconddiff,k=8)
## Warning in adf.test(seconddiff, k = 8): p-value smaller than printed p-value
## 
##  Augmented Dickey-Fuller Test
## 
## data:  seconddiff
## Dickey-Fuller = -8.5039, Lag order = 8, p-value = 0.01
## alternative hypothesis: stationary

According to ACF: non-seasonality q = 2, seasonality q = 1 According to PACF: non-seasonality p = 1, seasonality p = 2 difference: non-seasonality d = 2, seasonality p = 0

the data is stationary after differencing.

Using ARIMA(1,1,2)(1,0,0)[12]

original_ts %>%
  Arima(order=c(2,2,1),seasonal=c(1,0,1)) %>%
  residuals() %>%
  ggtsdisplay()
